quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  12,1,ALIF LAM RA. These are the verses (or symbols) of the Perspicuous (or clarifying) Book
  12,2,"Verily, We have revealed it as a Lecture (a Quran) in Arabic; per chance (or possibly) you may understand"
  12,3,"We tell you the best (the most beautiful, appealing, enlightening) of narratives in that We inspired in you this Quran, though you were before it among the heedless"
  12,4,"When Joseph said to his father, \"O my father! Verily, I saw (in my dream) eleven stars, and the sun, and the moon - I saw them prostrating themselves unto me"
  12,5,"He said, \"O my boy! Tell not your vision to your brethren, for they will plot against you. Verily, Satan is to man an open foe"
  12,6,"Thus your Lord will prefer you, and teach you the interpretation of events, and fulfil His favour upon you, and upon the family of Jacob, as He fulfiled it upon your two forefathers, Abraham and Isaac, before you. Verily, your Lord is Knowing, Wise"